metadata.name: 1 - Exploration
metadata.description:
My mother had eleven children.
I am the seventh of the nine who survived.
It is so strange to be here.
America is so different from Vietnam.
I bend my body and explore my surroundings, upside down. Will I understand California better this way?
He says I’m flexible and beautiful.
He says I must stay still.
His big camera takes time to adjust.
Beautiful I don’t know, I’m just a small-town girl, young and slim.
I am Thi Ha from Hoi An.
